CAPE TOWN - A former colleague of Cape Town mayor Patricia de Lille believes there's agenda against her. The Democratic Alliance suspended her last week for alleged maladministration. READ: DA suspends Patricia de Lille The party's federal executive has extended the deadline to 5 January for De Lille to give reasons why she shouldn’t resign as mayor. Former Independent Democrats deputy leader Simon Grindrod says it's disgraceful that she's being treated like a common criminal. * Watch the full video report by Leigh-Anne Jansen in the gallery above. eNCA